@nikita200: Works great, thanks for the upload!

@all: The average speed on this torrent that I got was 700kb/s. You might get more or less depending on the amount of seeders.

@crazysha: I have just downloaded and installed it on my laptop. Works and is indeed the real deal.

@dubai1991, @darkodar9, @rgshah3, @pjanil: This torrent is different from WINDOWS.8.ENTERPRISE-N because that one does not have Windows Media Player. This version from nikita200 has Windows Media Player built in.

@rgshah3: There are no other tools needed to install unless you want to boot from a USB, then you have to use a program (eg. Universal USB Installer). Otherwise, you can burn the .iso to a DVD and boot from the DVD.

@luciferps, @pirate4053: You can get the 32bit version of Windows 8 Enterprise from the same uploader (nikita200) here: http://thepiratebay.se/torrent/7505762/MICROSOFT.WINDOWS.8.ENTERPRISE.RTM.X86.VOLUME.ENGLISH.DVD-WZT

@mfmedia: I recommend that you use the 32bit version.

@myanktaker: The Enterprise version has more features than Pro. You can check out the differences here: http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Windows_8_editions

@SiN-R: All Windows 8 editions have the ability to use language packs.

@Rameyuk, @lekso: Yes, the .iso from this torrent is bootable.

@Equnax: When you activate it, the watermark at the bottom right corner will disappear.

@RMS043061: The above activation method works.

@pjanil, @topjimmy68, @demis1159, @ImSoJaded, @futopeti: You can activate Windows 8 using the guide below.

While in Desktop Mode, right click the bottom left corner. Click "Command Prompt (Admin)":

For Win 8 Enterprise:
slmgr /skms kms-c.no-ip.org:1688
slmgr.vbs -ato

For Win 8 Professional:
slmgr.vbs -ipk NG4HW-VH26C-733KW-K6F98-J8CK4
slmgr /skms kms-c.no-ip.org:1688
slmgr.vbs -ato 

Key to install Media Center(after you've installed Win 8 Pro):
RR3BN-3YY9P-9D7FC-7J4YF-QGJXW

@PirateWarden
Clicking "View details in Windows Activation" after activating the ENT version shows "Your license to use Windows expires on 2/2/2013" which is the same behaviour as the PRO version.

The thing about the enterprise version, at least with Windows 7, is that it is designed to periodically check in with a corporate KMS server.  If you remove a KMS-activated computer from the corporate environment, its activation will eventually expire.

